This paper is primarily focused on visual object tracking, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also makes use of deep learning techniques, which could place it under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The adaptive weighting of the saliency-based filter responses is a machine learning task, which could also place it under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which could place it under the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper deals with video processing, which could place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
